column4: Domino's Pizza, Inc. operates as a pizza company in the United States and internationally. The company operates through three segments: U.S. Stores, International Franchise, and Supply Chain. It offers pizzas under the Domino's brand name through company-owned and franchised stores. It provides bread products, wings, boneless chicken, pastas, oven-baked sandwiches, dips, soft drink products and desserts. Domino's Pizza, Inc. was founded in 1960 and is headquartered in Ann Arbor, Michigan.
